===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally {{m|zh|歀|tr=kuài}}, {{Han compound|ls=psc|柰|欠|c1=p|c2=s|t2=lacking, desire|nocap=yes|no_och=yes}}, meaning “desire”. The {{m|zh|木|tr=-}} component was simplified into {{m|zh|士|tr=-}} via {{w|libian}}, similar to {{m|zh|隸//|tr=-}}→{{m|zh|隷//|tr=-}}.<ref>李學勤，2012《字源》，天津：天津古籍出版社，2013年7月2次印刷。p. 768 </ref>

{{w|Shuowen Jiezi}} interprets it as {{Han compound|ls=psc|窾|欠|c1=p|c2=s|t2=lacking, desire|abb1=yes|nocap=yes}}.

